frameDefinitions: A Person usually resides or works in a Location.
A Figure is located relative to a Ground location.
A Landmark (in combination with the image schema evoked by particular targets) serves to pick out the final location of a Trajector in a construed or actual motion event.
An Agent acts to ensure that a Rule (often a constraint on behavior) is being followed.
A Current_country is identified as matching or not matching the instance of the Discourse_salient_country.
A Figure is located in the interior (the Profiled_region--see Locative_relation frame) of the Ground.
frameExamples: Flights <t>into</t> Denver are not permitted at this time.
Why don't we <t>enforce</t> the 20000 gun laws currently on the books across the nation?
<t><fex name='cur'>Foreign</fex></t> sales account for only 20% of IBM's income .
The bookmark <t>inside</t> her book was torn and written on .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Location</fen>  is the place of business or residence prototypically occupied by the <fen>Person</fen>.
The <fen>Person</fen> is located in or at a place that they customarily occupy.
The time period during which the <fen>Person</fen> occupies the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The <fen>Figures</fen> are items which mutually serve to identify the location of the other items.
The region within which a <fen>Figure</fen> might be found.  This role is exclusive of <fen>Figure</fen>, and is a reconstrual that is not possible with verb lexical units.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
The relatively locatable entity which serves as a basis for determining the location of the <fen>Trajector</fen> using the <fen>Profiled_region</fen>.
The location (located with respect to the <fen>Landmark</fen>) which is profiled by the particular image schema pertaining to the locative relation.
The entity which is construed to be in motion, whose location at the end of the construed motion event is in question.
The time at which the <fen>Trajector</fen> is located in the <fen>Profiled_region</fen>.
The <fen>Rule</fen> is the set of constrants on behavior that the <fen>Agent</fen> implements (i.e., forces others to obey or face consequences).
The <fen>Agent</fen>, often an institution, governmental organization, or arm thereof, puts into effect (i.e., enforces) a <fen>Rule</fen>.
This role describes the medium through which the rule was enforced.  It may occur in the same syntactic position as the Agent.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the Agent enforces the <fen>Rule</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Rule</fen> is or is not enforced.
The country or countries that the speaker is indicating in the current instance, which may match or be distinct from the <fen>Discourse_salient_country</fen>.

The country that has been featured in the discourse, or that the speaker/hearer identify with or are located in; it serves to identify the <fen>Current_country</fen> by specifying it as the same or different.  This role is incorporated in the targets of this frame.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is the entity located with respect to the <fen>Ground</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> is the area that the <fen>Figure</fen> is located in.
The area or zone interior to the <fen>Ground</fen>.  This role excludes <fen>Figure</fen> and is only used in particular constructions such as the following:
The time during which the <fen>Figure</fen> was located in the <fen>Ground</fen>.
listRoleExamples:
I couldn't access the details of prospective buyers and sellers and was
uncontactable when I was out <fex>of the office</fex>.
<fex>The doctor</fex> is not in right now.
Call work, tell them you'll be in <fex>in the afternoon</fex>.
<fex><t>Next to</t> the kitchen</fex> is the best place to locate your garage .
Employers should strictly enforce <fex>a prohibition against use of any substance that may affect a worker's physical or mental ability</fex>.
Can <fex>a landlord</fex> enforce rules upon tenants?
The rules will be enforced <fex>by a new computer system that tracks people's movements</fex>.
That particular regulation was only enforced <fex>in 1920</fex>.
For this reason they enforced the settlement system <fex>in America</fex> just as strictly as in Germany.
AutoPartsPlace.com offers discount prices on millions of import auto parts, <fex><t>domestic</t></fex> car parts, and car accessories.
Inside the cupboard was <fex>a good place to hide</fex> .
